  "title": "Heist at the Zoiby Auction House",
  "summary": "A quiet auction at the Zoiby Auction House on Etti IV erupts into chaos when an explosion in nearby Hydian Park draws away the ESPO security force. As panic empties the hall, the Twi'lek raider Twila seizes an ESPO lieutenant -- secretly the undercover officer Graden, playing the captive 'Hamlin' -- while seven masked gunmen storm the entrance and herd the remaining crowd onto the dais. Among those caught up are the ESPO Wuv, the surly swordsman Cubitt, and the off-duty pilot Gren Delede. The robbers fry the display cases with EMP grenades and loot the ancient artifacts, but the operation unravels when the masked leader proves willing to gun down his own men and the hostages. Cubitt, Wuv, Delede and the ESPOs turn on their captors in a swirling firefight; Twila is wounded and dragged to the getaway speeder, and the thieves finally escape with the artifacts, leaving smoke, wounded, and dead in their wake as Delede surveys the carnage.",
